*clicking on scenery which is set to be activateable calls a special script on the pointer to temporarily offset its position by 1 pixel to the left and fake a mouse click.
*the purpose of this is to stop the frustration of a click seeming to not register when clicking a dithered transparent object (such as any of the glass tubes)

*scrp 2 1 1 50200 (pointer redirect) is currently defined in "0.1_World_Overlays.cos"

scrp 1 11 50200 1

	inst

*set the OWNR in _P1_ so we can check against it in the pointer script
	mesg wrt+ pntr 50200 ownr 0 0

endm








